ch the value set in the Firewall profiles section.", "defaultValue": "Firewall config 1"}, {"key": "doFirewallProxy", "type": "CHOICE", "title": "Enable Proxy on device", "entries": [{"name": "None", "value": "NONE"}, {"name": "Use manual proxy configuration", "value": "STATIC"}, {"name": "Use proxy auto-config (PAC)", "value": "DYNAMIC"}], "description": "Use this control to enable or disable a global proxy on a device that routes all internet traffic through a proxy server of your choice. This works for both Wi-Fi and data connections. You can use either a fixed proxy server address or a proxy auto-config (PAC) file. According to your selection here, the settings provided in either the \"Manual proxy configuration\" or \"Proxy auto configuration\" section below will be used.", "defaultValue": "NONE"}]}, {"key": "doFotaUpdate", "type": "BUNDLE", "title": "Firmware update (FOTA) policy", "description": "A group of controls to configure firmware updates settings.", "nestedProperties": [{"key": "doFotaUpdateIsControlled", "type": "BOOL", "title": "Enable firmware controls", "description": "Use this control to enable or disable advanced firmware update options. If this control is disabled, any changes to other firmware update related settings have no impact.", "defaultValue": false}, {"key": "doFotaUpdateOTA", "type": "BOOL", "title": "Allow firmware update over-the-air", "description": "Use this control to enable or disable firmware updates using Firmware-Over-The-Air (FOTA) technology. When this policy controls is set to false, all possible OTA upgrade requests (user initiated, server initiated, and system initiated) are blocked; the user may see server messages related to new firmware updates but any attempt to upgrade fails. This does not block user from updating firmware using recovery mode.", "defaultValue": true}, {"key": "doFotaUpdateRecoveryMode", "type": "BOOL", "title": "Allow firmware update in recovery mode", "description": "Use this control to enable or d