description": "Use this control to stop applications from showing notifications on the status bar. When this policy is enabled, notifications from all applications in the workspace are blocked except for the apps specified in this allowlist. Enter the values as a comma separated list or wildcard to specify multiple apps to the allowlist, if you want to use advanced query, please use correct regular expression syntax.", "defaultValue": ""}, {"key": "poAppMgmtInstallApp", "type": "STRING", "title": "Install app from personal to work profile", "description": "Use this control to install an existing application from the personal (default) space into the Work Profile, without requiring user interaction.", "defaultValue": ""}, {"key": "poAppMgmtToAllowUSBDeviceAccessForApps", "type": "BOOL", "title": "Allow USB Devices for default access by Application (Configure profiles below)", "description": "Use this setting to grant user permission for one or more usb devices to be used by a particular package. Use the Allowed USB devices for Applications section for Configurations.", "defaultValue": false}, {"key": "poAppMgmtWhitelistAppByName", "type": "STRING", "title": "Application Allowlist by Pkg Name", "description": "Use this control to allowlist applications to be installed on the PO. When this policy is enabled, third-party application (application that is not part of system image) based on the application package name will be allowlisted. Enter the values as a comma separated list or wildcard to specify multiple apps to the allowlist, if you want to use advanced query, please use correct regular expression syntax. If the package name of an application currently being installed matches a package name pattern in both the blocklist and allowlist, the allowlist takes priority and the application is installed.", "defaultValue": ""}, {"key": "poAppMgmtBlacklistAppByName", "type": "STRING", "title": "Application Blocklist by Pkg Name", "description": "Use this control to blocklist applications to be installed on the PO. When this policy is enabled, third-party application (application that is not part of system image) based on the application package name will be blocklisted. Enter the values as a comma separated list or wildcard to specify multiple apps to the blocklist, if you want to use advanced query, please use correct regular expression syntax. If the application package is already installed, the API does not affect the existing installation.", "defaultValue": ""}, {"key": "poAppMgmtWhitelistAppBySignature", "type": "STRING", "title": "Application Allowlist by Signature used", "description": "Use this control to allowlist applications to be installed on the PO. When this policy is enabled, third-party application (application that is not part of system image) based on the signature used by the application will be allowlisted. Enter the values as a comma separated list or wildcard to specify multiple apps to the allowlist. If the signature of an application currently being installed matches the signature in both the blocklist and allowlist, the allowlist takes priority and the application is installed.", "defaultValue": ""}, {"key": "poAppMgmtBlacklistAppBySignature", "type": "STRING", "title": "Application Blocklist by Signature used", "description": "Use this control to blocklist applications to be installed on the PO. When this policy is enabled, third-party application (application that is not part of system image) based on the signature used by the application will be blocklisted. Enter the values as a comma separated list or wildcard to specify multiple apps to the blocklist. If the application package is already installed, the API does not affect the existing installation.", "defaultValue": ""}, {"key": "poAppMgmtDisableApp", "type": "STRING", "title": "Disable Application without user interaction", "description": "Use this control to disable application without user interaction. The disabled application package is not uninstalled but the device user cannot use it. The API does not affect the future application package state. Enter the values as a comma separated list, for example, \"com.xyz, com.abc\".", "defaultValue": ""}, {"key": "poAppMgmtForceStopBlacklist", "type": "STRING", "title": "Force Stop Blocklist", "description": "Use this control to prevent the user from stopping certain applications. The stop actions include force stop in Settings app, stopping through third-party applications, stopping any background process by system and stopping any service from the application. Enter the values as a comma separated list or wildcard to specify multiple apps to the blocklist, if you want to use advanced query, please use correct regular expression syntax.", "defaultValue": ""}, {"key": "poAppMgmtAutoLaunchApp", "type": "STRING", "title": "Package Name for Auto-Launch", "description": "Enter the package name of the application that needs to be launched after it is installed along with the Component name. Example: PackageName/ComponentName", "defaultValue": ""}, {"key": "poAppMgmtClearCacheBlocklist", "type": "STRING", "title": "Clear Cache Block List", "description": "Use this control to prevent the user from clearing cache for certain applications. The actions include clear cache in Settings app, clearing cache through third-party applications, and clearing service cache from the application. Also, wildcard characters like \"com.xyz.*\" can be used to specify multiple application package names.", "defaultValue": ""}, {"key": "poAppMgmtClearDataBlocklist", "type": "STRING", "title": "Clear Data Block List", "description": "Use this control to prevent the user from clearing data for certain applications. The actions include clear data in Settings app, clearing data through third-party applications, and clearing service data from the application. Also, wildcard characters like \"com.xyz.*\" can be used to specify multiple application package names.", "defaultValue": ""}]}, {"key": "poAuditLog", "type": "BUNDLE", "title": "Audit Log (Premium)", "description": "A group of controls to enable audit log on the device. Available with a KPE Premium license.", "nestedProperties": [{"key": "poAuditLogIsControlled", "type": "BOOL", "title": "Enable Audit Log", "description": "Use this control to enable audit log to capture events such as Password policies set for devices; App installation and removal; Certificate failure and key generation; Account creation and removal; File exchange attempts over Wi-Fi etc", "defaultValue": false}, {"key": "poAuditLogPolicyConfig", "type": "BUNDLE", "title": "Audit Log Policy Configuration", "description": "A group of controls to configure audit log on the device. Available with a KPE Premium license", "nestedProperties": [{"key": "poAuditLogPolicies", "type": "MULTISELECT", "title": "Audit Log Policies", "entries": [{"name": "All Group", "value": "ALL"}, {"name": "Application Group", "value": "APPLICATION"}, {"name": "Events Group", "value": "EVENTS"}, {"name": "Network Group", "value": "NETWORK"}, {"name": "Security Group", "value": "SECURITY"}, {"name": "System Group", "value": "SYSTEM"}], "description": "Use this control to select granular audit log on the device", "defaultValue": ["ALL"]}, {"key": "poAuditLogOutcome", "type": "CHOICE", "title": "Audit Log Outcome", "entries": [{"name": "All", "value": "ALL"}, {"name": "Failures", "value": "FAILURE"}, {"name": "Successes", "value": "SUCCESS"}], "description": "Use this control to select audit log outcome on the device", "defaultValue": "ALL"}, {"key": "poAuditLogSeverityLevel", "type": "CHOICE", "title": "Audit Log Severity Level", "entries": [{"name": "All", "value": "ALL"}, {"name": "Alert", "value": "ALERT"}, {"name": "Critical", "value": "CRITICAL"}, {"name": "Error", "value": "ERROR"}, {"name": "Warning", "value": "WARNING"}], "description": "Use this control to select severity level of Audit Log", "defaultValue": "CRITICAL"}, {"key": "poAuditLogFrequency", "type": "CHOICE", "title": "Audit Log Frequency", "entries": [{"name": "2 Hours", "value": "2"}, {"name": "6 Hours", "value": "6"}, {"name": "12 Hours", "value": "12"}, {"name": "24 Hours", "value": "24"}], "description": "Use this control to select the Audit log frequency", "defaultValue": "6"}]}]}, {"key": "poCertificatePolicy", "type": "BUNDLE", "title": "Certificate management policies (Premium)", "description": "A group of policies to control certificate management settings. For example, disable certificates, restrict certificates and more.", "nestedProperties": [{"key": "poCertificatePolicyIsControlled", "type": "BOOL", "title": "Enable certificate management controls", "description": "Use this control to enable or disable certificate management settings for the workspace. Enable this control before changing any certificate management settings. If this control is not enabled, any Enterprise certificate management policy is ignored.", "defaultValue": false}, {"key": "poCertificatePolicyRevoke", "type": "BUNDLE", "title": "Certificate revocation", "description": "Choose the Certificate revocation method most appropriate for your workspace.", "nestedProperties": [{"key": "poCertificatePolicyEnableRevoke", "type": "CHOICE", "title": "Enable revocation check", "entries": [{"name": "Not enabled", "value": "DISABLE"}, {"name": "Enable for all apps", "value": "ALL_APPLICATIONS"}, {"name": "Enable for specified apps only", "value": "SELECTED_APPLICATIONS"}], "description": "Use this to check certificate validation. For example if you list \"com.samsung.email\" in a allowlist, any certificates used by this app for SMIME encryption or signing is first checked against a list of Certificate Revocation List (CRL) to verify that they are still valid. Enter the application package names to check as a comma separated list, for example (\"com.xyz, com.abc\")", "defaultValue": "DISABLE"}, {"key": "poCertificatePolicyEnableOCSP", "type": "BOOL", "title": "Enable OCSP check before CRL", 