led, any Dual DAR policy settings you change are ignored and the device may use Dual DAR with default values.", "defaultValue": false}, {"key": "poDualDarTimeoutType", "type": "CHOICE", "title": "Data lock timeout type", "entries": [{"name": "No lock-out", "value": "NO_LOCKOUT"}, {"name": "Specified value", "value": "SPECIFIED_VALUE"}], "description": "Use this control to set a data lock type. This locks the credential encrypted (CE) storage and flushes the key from memory. Once locked, apps can''t use the CE until user provides the credential again.", "defaultValue": "NO_LOCKOUT"}, {"key": "poDualDarTimeoutValue", "type": "STRING", "title": "Data lock timeout value (in minutes)", "description": "Use this control to specify the data lock timeout value in minutes. To use this feature, you must set the data lock timeout type to \"specified value.\"", "defaultValue": "1"}, {"key": "poDualDarRestrictDe", "type": "BOOL", "title": "Restrict access to device encrypted (DE) storage", "description": "Use this control to enable or disable access restrictions to the DE storage. By default, apps in the DualDAR area are allowed to access the DE storage. Enabling this control prevents apps, other than those allowlisted by Admin, to access DE storage.", "defaultValue": false}, {"key": "poDualDarRestrictDeApps", "type": "STRING", "title": "List of apps allowed to access DE storage and to run in data locked state", "description": "Use this control to specify the list of apps that are allowed to access DE storage and to run in data locked state.", "defaultValue": ""}]}, {"key": "poFirewallPolicy", "type": "BUNDLE", "title": "Firewall policy (Premium)", "description": "A group of policies for firewall setup and configuration. IT admins can enforce these policies for devices with a Work profile.", "nestedProperties": [{"key": "poFirewallIsControlled", "type": "BOOL", "title": "Enable firewall controls", "description": "Use this control to enable or disable the firewall controls for the Work profile.", "defaultValue": false}, {"key": "poFirewallConfigName", "type": "STRING", "title": "Name of firewall configuration to use", "description": "Enter the name of the primary firewall configuration profile that apps can use for network connections. This profile name must match the value set in the Firewall profiles section.", "defaultValue": "Firewall config 1"}]}, {"key": "poNPA", "type": "BUNDLE", "title": "Network Platform Analytics (NPA) (Premium)", "description": "A group of controls to enable and configure NPA clients to collect network activity data on the device. Available with a KPE Premium license.", "nestedProperties": [{"key": "poNPAIsControlled", "type": "BOOL", "title": "Enable NPA Controls", "description": "Use this control to allow your NPA client to collect network activity data on the device. Enable this option before you specify any other options for your NPA client.", "defaultValue": false}, {"key": "poNPAClient", "type": "CHOICE", "title": "NPA Client", "entries": [{"name": "Cisco Connect", "value": "0"}], "description": "Select the NPA Client that can collect network activity data on the device.", "defaultValue": "0"}, {"key": "poNPADataPointsProfile", "type": "STRING", "title": "NPA Profile for Data Points", "description": "Enter the name of the profile that specifies the data points you want the NPA Client to collect. This profile name must match the ''Profile Name'' value set in the NPA Data Points Profile section.", "defaultValue": "NPA profile 1"}]}, {"key": "poPasswordPolicy", "type": "BUNDLE", "title": "Password Policy (Premium)", "description": "A group of policies to manage password policies on the device, including enabling or disabling the ability to manage passwords and other authentication methods to log in to the Work profile. These policies apply to all devices with a Work profile.", "nestedProperties": [{"key": "poPasswordIsControlled", "type": "BOOL", "title": "Enable password policy controls with KSP", "description": "For devices with a Work profile, use this control to allow management of password policies on the Work profile. Enable this option before changing any related settings. If this option is not enabled, any settings for password and authentication related items are ignored.", "defaultValue": false}, {"key": "poPasswordBiometric", "type": "BUNDLE", "title": "Biometric authentication", "description": "A group of policies to manage the biometric authentication options without user interaction. Knox Workspace does not use facial recognition as an authentication method.", "nestedProperties": [{"key": "poPasswordBioFp", "type": "BOOL", "title": "Enable fingerprint authentication", "description": "Use this control to allow or stop the use of fingerprint recognition for authentication.", "defaultValue": true}, {"key": "poPasswordBioIris", "type": "BOOL", "title": "Enable Iris authentication", "description": "Use this control to allow or stop the use of iris recognition for authentication.", "defaultValue": true}, {"key": "poPasswordBioFace", "type": "BOOL", "title": "Enable Face recognition", "description": "Use this control to allow or stop the use of facial recognition for authentication.", "defaultValue": true}]}, {"key": "poPasswordMultifactorAuth", "type": "BOOL", "title": "Enable multifactor authentication", "description": "Use this control to enable or disable multifactor authentication (2FA). Once enabled, the workspace is only unlocked after two authentication methods are provided, including one biometric input (iris / fingerprint) and one lock screen method (PIN / password / pattern). This feature is available only on Knox 3.2.1 and above. *Note: Incorrect use of this policy together with \"One Lock\" and \"Biometric policy\" can lock your device.", "defaultValue": false}, {"key": "poPasswordChange", "type": "BUNDLE", "title": "Password Change (Premium)", "description": "A group of policies to manage password change.", "nestedProperties": [{"key": "poPasswordChangeEnforce", "type": "BOOL", "title": "Enforce Password Change", "description": "Use this control to enforce password change. if no password set, enforce to set. Caution: Verify password enforcement condition before saving any new policy otherwise it will enforce password at unexpected time", "defaultValue": false}, {"key": "poPasswordChangeEnforceTimeout", "type": "INTEGER", "title": "Password Enforcement timeout", "description": "Enter the value in mins up to which user can cancel/delay the password change", "defaultValue": 0}]}, {"key": "poPasswordRestriction", "type": "BUNDLE", "title": "Password Restriction", "description": "A group of policies to manage password restriction.", "nestedProperties": [{"key": "poPasswordMaxCharacterSequenceLength", "type": "INTEGER", "title": "Maximum Character Sequence Length", "description": "Use this policy to specify the maximum length of an alphabetic sequence that is allowed for the work profile.", "defaultValue": 0}, {"key": "poPasswordMaxNumericSequenceLength", "type": "INTEGER", "title": "Maximum Numeric Sequence Length", "description": "Use this policy to specify the maximum length of numeric sequence that is allowed for the work profile.", "defaultValue": 0}, {"key": "poPasswordMinLength", "type": "INTEGER", "title": "Minimum Password Length", "description": "Use this policy to specify minimum length password allowed for the profile.", "defaultValue": 0}]}, {"key": "poPasswordMaxTimeToWorkProfileLock", "type": "INTEGER", "title": "Allowed Time for User Activity before Work Profile Locks", "description": "Enter the maximum number of time in seconds for user activity until the work profile will lock. A Value of 0 means there is no restriction; *Note: The API takes into effect immediately.", "defaultValue": 0}, {"key": "poPasswordMaxFailedAttemptToWipeData", "type": "INTEGER", "title": "Maximum Failed Password Attempt to Wipe Data", "description": "Enter the maximum number of failed password allowed until the data in the wo